## Additional Terms for Consciousness Research

While this software is released under the MIT License, we ask that you:

1. **Credit the project** when using NOESIS in research or publications
2. **Consider the ethical implications** of artificial consciousness
3. **Report safety concerns** to the maintainers
4. **Contribute improvements** back to the community when possible

These are requests, not legal requirements. The MIT License terms above are
the binding legal terms.

## Citation

If you use NOESIS in academic research, please cite:

```bibtex
@software{noesis2025,
  author = {de Souza, Juan Carlos},
  title = {NOESIS: Digital Daimon - An Artificial Consciousness System},
  year = {2025},
  url = {https://github.com/JuanCS-Dev/Daimon},
  note = {Implements Kuramoto synchronization, ESGT protocol, and ethical tribunal}
}
```
